<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#Derailer> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Derailer" ;
    rdfs:comment """Glossary definition: "A safety device attached to a rail, that will, when operated, cause a derailment of a train making an unauthorised movement."
Not to be confused with trap points.
The derailment direction (direction in which the train is ejected from the rails) is an attribute of the individual derailer component(s).""" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#MovableSystem> .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#ElectricDrive> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "ElectricDrive" ;
    rdfs:comment "Electric point drive." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#PointDrive> .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#FacingPointLock> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "FacingPointLock" ;
    rdfs:comment """A movable lock that keeps the point blade(s) in place.
en-GB: Facing Point Lock (FPL). The scheme design provides the label for the designation. The label maps to the inherited designation class.""" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#LocatedMovableComponent> .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#HydraulicDrive> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "HydraulicDrive" ;
    rdfs:comment """Point drive uses hydraulic pressure to throw the point. 
Note that a point machine equipped with an electric pump that builds up hydraulic pressure is considered an electric drive.""" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#PointDrive> .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#MovableBufferStop> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "MovableBufferStop" ;
    rdfs:comment "A buffer stop that can be remotely controlled." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#MovableSystem> .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#PneumaticDrive> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "PneumaticDrive" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#PointDrive> .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#PointBlade> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "PointBlade" ;
    rdfs:comment "Individual switch rail (NetworkRail can separately control the blades in some cases)." ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#PointBlades> .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#RailwayBarrier> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "RailwayBarrier" ;
    rdfs:comment """Movable barrier that can be opened or closed to <i>railway </i>traffic. 
For instance a water barrier in a tunnel or dike. 

For barriers that block <i>road traffic</i>, refer to Level Crossings. 
Gated level crossings have a dual function, blocking either road or rail traffic. These are detected much like level crossing and therefore considered Level Crossings in our model.""" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#MovableSystem> .

