<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Working_safety#scheme_LockoutDeviceTypes_EAID_694D2FDE_D466_4a06_AA5E_055150FBFF1E> a skos:ConceptScheme ;
    rdfs:label "LockoutDeviceTypes" ;
    rdfs:comment """d
Disallows main route setting into the lockout area but shunting movements are allowed.""",
        """e
Similar to type k except that the key is in possession of platform staff and sometimes siding staff.""",
        """k
Removing the captive key prevents train movements in both directions.""",
        """o
Like type "k" except that authorised staff keeps the keys that activate the lockout devices in a lockout area.""",
        """p
Protects line-side workers, patrol men, by preventing train movement in the wrong direction.""",
        """switchLock
Old type of lockout device.""" .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/ProRail/Common#TunnelTechnicalInstallation> a owl:Class ;
