<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/ETCS#EtcsMarker> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "EtcsMarker" ;
    rdfs:comment """An ETCS marker is a spot on the track where a linear event occurs or a property changes that is relevant to ETCS signalling:
<ul>
	<li>Change in National Values</li>
	<li>Change of gradient</li>
	<li>Change of speed</li>
	<li>Change of track condition</li>
	<li>Start of text display</li>
</ul>

An ETCS profile is an ordered sequence of markers.""" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Train_protection#TpMarker> .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/ETCS#LeuPort> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "LeuPort" ;
    rdfs:comment """Port between LEU and individually-controlled balise.
The planned and as-built port may differ due to the planning process. Both numbers are stored.""" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:onProperty <https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/ETCS#plannedNumber> ;
            owl:someValuesFrom xsd:integer ],
