fr-FR: Abr&#233;viations de la d&#233;signation des champs li&#233;s au contr&#244;le de vitesse.

Source: SNCF document IG90169, paragraph 6.3.2""" .

<https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#MovableElement> a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "MovableElement" ;
    rdfs:comment "The movable element is an abstraction that associates the underlying movable components with the mechanism(s) that move them. The signaller selects and operates one movable element and needn't be concerned with the underlying individual components of the movable element.",
        """canReportDegradedStatus
True: this movable element can report a degraded status which means a loss of full detection. This is a function of the reports from the individual detectors, some of which may be crucial or not.""" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
